  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally involves financial transactions designed to conceal the origin of illegally obtained money. Specific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but typically include:\n\n1. Core Elements:\n- Concealing the source of criminal proceeds\n- Transforming illegal funds into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Disguising the true ownership or origin of funds\n\n2. Common Legal Components:\n- Intentional transfer of funds from criminal activities\n- Attempting to make illegal funds appear legal\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide criminal origins\n\n3. General Stages:\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into financial system)\n- Layering (creating complex transactions to obscure origins)\n- Integration (reintroducing funds as seemingly legitimate)\n\nKey specifics can vary between countries' legal codes. For precise definitions, consulting local financial crime statutes is recommended.\n\nI aim to provide accurate general information about legal concepts while avoiding specific advisory roles.",
